properties.areaDesc: West Slopes South Central Cascades and Passes; West Slopes North Central Cascades and Passes; West Slopes North Cascades and Passes
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 1 at 3:04AM PST until January 2 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Rain will transition to snow during the day today
resulting in snow accumulations over the Cascades. Total snow
accumulations of 2 to 6 inches above 3000 feet and 8 to 14
inches above 4000 feet.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains of Whatcom, Skagit, Snohomish, King,
Pierce, and Lewis Counties, including the Mount Baker Ski Area,
Stevens Pass, Snoqualmie Pass, the Crystal Mountain Ski Area,
Paradise on Mount Rainier, and White Pass.

* WHEN...From 1 PM this afternoon to 4 AM PST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be difficult at times over the mountain
passes.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow levels will fall to 3000 to 4000 feet
this afternoon and evening.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT FROM 1 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 4 AM PST THURSDAY ABOVE 3000 FEET
